 in the heavens. \" data-chomp-id=\"b49865e5e53d1e5879246ecff16a7f20\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"738\" data-alt=\"Travelers look at a goddess in the heavens. \" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/b49865e5e53d1e5879246ecff16a7f20.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Sandfall Interactive\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"b49865e5e53d1e5879246ecff16a7f20\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b49865e5e53d1e5879246ecff16a7f20\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1313\" data-height=\"738\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Travelers look at a goddess in the heavens. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhile Xbox Game Pass rarely goes a month without getting at least something new that’s worth checking out, it’s certainly \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/xbox-game-pass-subscriber-numbers-2022-xbox-series-x-s-1848963643\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/xbox-game-pass-subscriber-numbers-2022-xbox-series-x-s-1848963643\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehad its dry spells\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e in recent years. The back half of January, however, has quietly revealed a surprising number of cool new games hitting the Netflix-like subscription service, and with several more day-and-date releases announced during \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/xbox-developer-direct-doom-dark-ages-ninja-gaiden-1851746052\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/xbox-developer-direct-doom-dark-ages-ninja-gaiden-1851746052\"\u003eThursday’s Xbox Developer Direct\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, 2025 is looking like it might be one of th